The Brandon University Bobcats women’s volleyball team upset the host University of Calgary Dinos on Friday to collect their first win of Canada West conference play. 
Shanlee McLennan posted 13 kills, three blocks and 11 digs to lead the Bobcats to a 3-1 (25-23, 20-25, 25-16, 25-23) victory over the Dinos, who are ranked eighth in Canadian Interuniversity Sport. Breanne Sytnyk and Regan Dahl both posted 12 kills while Jodie Baker terminated 10 balls and posted six blocks for Brandon (1-2). Mary Thomson had 45 assists and served four aces in the match.
